description.content:
Function called when flag is being added to an item. file.*ext.item.*itemType.*flagName.add. For example: a hook file.js.item.function.param.add would be called when processing param flag and adding it to already identified function.
This hook is also called with flagName equal to item type: file.js.item.function.function.add. In its generic version this hook sets item name from the content of this flag.

Function called after flag is added to an item. file.*ext.item.*itemType.*flagName.added. For example: a hook file.js.item.function.param.added would be called when finished processing param flag and added it to already identified function.
Some flags may require specific parsing.
Prepare flag content if it needs preparing. For example flags with no content become boolean flags, so if content == null we return true.

Plugin name

Call a plugin function and pass parameters to it. Plugins are js files from local hooks directory (or one of your directories) containing functions, scalar values and any other stuff. The file structure is like file/js/item/param/add.js which is called when adding parameter to js function. Plugins can be generic: file/* /item/* /* /add.js . Plugins are stored in globalCache var and can be overriden/intercepted etc.

Internally, it uses pget to find the plugin.

Called from SourceFile it looks for file/-ext-/-name- plugins. Called from Item it looks for file/-item-file-ext-/item/-current-item-type-/-name- and if not found - generics. First item_type generic, then file_ext generic.

Also, there is '?' plugin directories for unknown-type items.
